  "description": [
    "Page Two THE AUGUSTA COURIER He who spores no class of men is angry at no person but the vices of all 1300 Southern Finance Building Augusta Georgia SecondClass Postage Paid at Augusta Georgia SUBSCRIPTION RATE Published Weekly by The Courier Publishing Company Year 400 IS U S PLAYING CUBAN ROULETTE The Augusta Ga Herald November 5 1962 The United States proceeding largely on faith and aerial reconnais sance may be playing a game of Cuban Roulette in accepting at face value Russian promises that the nuclear missiles it has planted on Cuban soil are being removed President Kennedy has given the people of this country strong re assurance that the dismantling of these menacing weapons is proceeding as promised We sincerely hope that this is so But on the same day that Kennedy was giving the US this reassurance a disturbing report came out of Castroland delivered by Rafael GarciaNovarro an exiled Cuban official This messagetoGarcia in reverse one might almost call it was to the effect that Fidel Castro is openly dismantling intermediate range missiles while stalling for time to get other missiles of shorter range hidden in mountain caves and excavations to escape the probing eyes of"
  ],
